p: In conclusion, dietary supplementation with a combination of 15% corn oil, 10% coconut oil, 15% linseed oil, 20% palm oil, 15% peanut oil, and 25% soybean oil had positive effects on ADG, FCR, liver percentage, serum glucose, total serum protein and meat quality, as well as higher SFAs and PUFAs deposition in breast muscle of broilers, which indicates these two mixed plant oils can be used as better dietary energy feedstocks than soybean oil alone.
